                <head>No. 301<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The final item discussed by the Foreign Ministers during the afternoon session on
                    October 16 was the date for the next meeting of the North Atlantic Council,
                    which was to be held in Paris. <persName corresp="#p_BGP1">Bidault</persName>
                    stated that the French Presidential elections might interfere with a December
                    session, but promised to advise his colleagues further. (<gloss
                        target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 9 from London, October 16, 396.1
                    LO/10–1653) The following day <persName corresp="#p_BGP1">Bidault</persName>
                    reported that December 17–20 appeared to be the best dates for the meeting and
                    promised to do his best to keep the French elections from conflicting with it.
                        (<gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 18 from London, October 17, 396.1
                    LO/10–1753)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
